text:
Good place for Hong Kong dessert. My local friends said that it was very tasty.

We just came for the dessert and everything was very good.
The mala fish and the desserts are good. I thought the wet tissue was complimentary.

Dishes were overpriced. Ordered cereal chicken and a 3 egg spinach with two rice n two ice tea cost $43 plus but thatâ€™s not the worse, the chicken tasted like cardboard marinated and deep fried with cereal and the spinach veggies was blend and tasteless ! Shameful to serve and lack pride totally tobe running a restaurant! One of the worst I have tasted
Ordered the CNY Dinner 2020. Enjoyed it well. Slightly expensive due to the festival. Extra order Deep fried Yam Ball and Spicy Chicken Cube. Totally worthy.

The food was very meh, three egg spinach at $13 for a small portion was bland, cereal chicken was chewy with no curry leaf, just tasted of breakfast chicken ($20 for a small portion!). For these prices I expect food with taste.
